RELIABILITY_SLA:
  Availability: 99.5%
    - Downtime budget: 43 minutes/month
    - Maintenance window: 1 hour/week (off-peak)
    - Exceeding budget: Auto-credit 10% service fee
  
  Error rate: < 0.1%
    - 1 error per 1000 requests maximum
    - Exceeding: Automatic incident investigation
  
  Data durability: 99.99999% (7 nines)
    - RTO (Recovery Time Objective): < 15 minutes
    - RPO (Recovery Point Objective): < 1 minute data loss
    - Tested monthly via DR drills
  
  Webhook delivery:
    - First attempt success: 99%
    - With exponential backoff retries: 99.99%
    - Max 5 retries over 24 hours

THROUGHPUT_REQUIREMENTS:
  
  Webhook ingestion:
    - 10,000 webhooks/second (Stripe rate limit)
    - Peak handling: 50,000/second (5x buffer)
    - Queueing: Kafka with 3x replication
  
  Email processing:
    - 100,000 emails/day (Gmail integration)
    - Peak: 10 emails/second
    - Queue: Exponential backoff if Gmail rate-limited
  
  Agent execution:
    - 50,000 agent tasks/day per customer
    - Concurrent agent limit: 10 per customer (prevent runaway)
    - Timeout: 30 seconds per agent execution
  
  Database connections:
    - Max concurrent: 500 (pgBouncer limit)
    - Per customer: 20 connections max
    - Overflow: Queue requests, timeout after 5 seconds

FAILURE_HANDLING_SLA:
  
  Agent failures:
    - Transient error (network timeout): Retry 3x with exponential backoff
    - Permanent error (validation): Fail immediately, log + alert
    - Timeout (> 30s): Kill agent, revert partial changes, log + alert
    - Customer data corruption: CRITICAL alert, disable agent, manual review required
  
  External API failures (Stripe, Gmail, Twitter):
    - Connection timeout: Retry with exponential backoff
    - Rate limited (429): Respect Retry-After header, queue request
    - Service down (5xx): Circuit breaker opens, queue for later
    - Degradation: Partial success, log + alert (not critical)
  
  Database failures:
    - Primary down: Auto-failover to replica (< 30 seconds)
    - All replicas down: CRITICAL, activate disaster recovery
    - Connection pool exhausted: Queue requests, fail gracefully (429)
    - Query timeout (> 30s): Kill query, log + alert, retry with simpler query